data.name: EM Sullivan
data.description:
E.M. Sullivan Associates, Inc. was founded in 1972 as a specialty chemical distributor and sales agent. Technically oriented and focused on marketing our principal’s products, we strive to exceed customer expectations and find synergies between principles and customers. Our primary goal is to offer a unique perspective and expertise in finding innovative solutions for technically challenging issues in manufacturing today.

Over 40 years later, E.M. Sullivan’s next generation of leaders continue to grow this company into a full-service specialty chemical distributor with a North American sales region, with corporate offices outside of Philadelphia. Distribution excellence is accomplished with our multiple warehouse locations. Our state-of- the-art distribution system is capable of safe and accurate warehousing of all material types. We are able to expedite shipping, handle emergency situations and customize distribution to meet our customer’s specific needs.

Helping to develop the next “market leaders” with technological advances is an on-going goal at EM Sullivan. As consolidations continue with all segments of the economy, innovation becomes a secondary concern to the bottom line. We at Sullivan feel that innovation is the bottom line.

data.name: ADINS
data.description: ADINS® additives, based on functionalized uncommon silicate with a needle-like structure (sepiolite), allow to improve the fire performance of polymeric formulations.

data.name: ASCONIUM® 141S1
data.description: ASCONIUM® 141S1 is a liquid anticorrosion additive for metal coatings, replacing mineral anticorrosion pigments or enhancing their performance in waterborne or solvent borne metal coatings. It acts as a hydrophobic agent, improving dry-film's water resistance.

data.name: Unicryl PCX PP 16
data.description: Unicryl PCX PP 16 is a powdered superplasticizer based on polycarboxylate ether chemistry. It is designed for dry-mix cementitious products.

data.name: Tytan™ CA-B116
data.description: Tytan™ CA-B116 serves as a replacement for PU catalysts, particularly for tin-based catalysts such as DBTL, in one- and two-component polyurethane systems. Notably, it demonstrates compatibility with secondary alcohols, offering enhanced performance in various applications.

data.name: DeTERGE LF - 7315

summary.name: Certifications & Compliance
items: Comprehensive Environmental Response, Compensations & Liability Act (CERCLA)

data.description: DeTERGE LF - 7315 is a low-foaming, modified amphoteric surfactant ideal for highly alkaline and acidic systems. It functions effectively as the primary surfactant, offering wetting and detergency in both acidic and alkaline environments. Its excellent solubility may eliminate the need for a hydrotrope. Moreover, it is biodegradable, non-phenolic, and phosphate-free.

data.name: DeTERGE CS - 45LF
data.description: DeTERGE CS - 45LF is an exceptional, cost-effective, low-foaming surfactant resistant to chlorine. It's formulated for products containing up to 15% active caustic and other alkaline electrolytes. Chemically classified as an alkoxylated carboxylate, it's intended solely for use in alkaline systems and not recommended for acid systems.

data.name: Polidene® 777
data.description: Polidene® 777 is an aqueous anionic copolymer emulsion specifically engineered for applications in specialty paints and protective coating production.

data.name: ASCOTRUST® X3
data.description: ASCOTRUST® X3 is a liquid additive designed for waterborne coatings. It reacts with metal cations to form stable organic complexes that chemically bond to metal substrates, providing stable and effective chemical passivation.

data.name: Afcona 3238
data.description: Afcona - 3238 is an additive designed as a slip and leveling agent that also offers defoaming properties.

data.name: Vinavil 5706
data.description: Vinavil 5706 is an elastomeric copolymer styrene acrylic with high solids content.

Pangel products are highly pseudoplastic additives based in different silicate minerals for both water and solvent based systems.

data.name: Pangel® B10
data.description: Pangel® B10 is a product designed to effectively control the rheological properties of a system. Its micro-fibers form a reticulated, stable, and homogeneous network, Pangel® B10 enables the achievement of a pseudoplastic behavior and an optimal gel structure in the coating.

data.name: Pangel® B20
data.description: Pangel® B20 is a rheological additive derived from sepiolite (hydrated magnesium silicate), with its particle surface organically modified to ensure compatibility with medium and low polarity systems or solvents. It forms a three-dimensional network of particles, enhancing the viscosity and thixotropy of the end product. In epoxy coatings, Pangel® B20 offers the option for partial or complete substitution of fumed silicas and organophilic bentonites typically used as rheological additives, presenting additional cost-effective benefits in formulations.

data.name: Pangel® B42
data.description: Pangel® B42 is characterized by its cream to greyish color and possesses a slight odor reminiscent of isopropanol and amines.

data.name: Pangel® B5
data.description: Pangel® B5 is an effective additive utilized in crumb rubber-modified asphalt applications. Its inclusion results in homogeneous mixes, reducing variations in properties such as penetration, softening point, and solid content, particularly after dissolving bitumen in solvents like Tetrahydrofuran. This additive ensures the stability of asphalt crumb rubber mixes even after storage at elevated temperatures, effectively preventing settling issues.

data.name: Pangel® M90F
data.description: Pangel® M90F is a high-purity smectite-based additive with a selected particle size, specifically designed to adjust the rheology of joint compounds, plasters, and fillers formulated in both powder and paste. It is recommended for applications requiring a fine particle size. Additionally, Pangel® M90F can serve as a binding agent for both organic and inorganic powders. Its high swelling capacity upon contact with water allows it to disperse easily while retaining high resistance when dry.

data.name: Pangel® OM4
data.description: Pangel® OM4 is a rheological additive designed for intermediate to low polarity systems, formulated with highly purified bentonite clay. It's suitable for use with aliphatic solvents as well as mineral or synthetic oils. This standard organo-bentonite requires pregel preparation using a polar activator, making it ideal for low to medium-polarity solvent-based systems.

data.name: Pangel® C150
data.description: Pangel® C150 is a rheological additive crafted from sepiolite. As a powder additive, it enhances system rheology.

data.name: Pangel® W
data.description: Pangel® W is a rheological additive meticulously engineered to induce robust pseudoplastic behavior in any formulation it is incorporated into. Pangel® W range is specifically formulated to serve as a thickener and water retention additive in emulsion paints.

data.name: Pangel® S9
data.description: Pangel® S9 is a highly efficient powder rheological additive made from high-purity sepiolite, suitable for aqueous systems. It serves as a gelling and suspending agent for high and medium-polarity systems. Pangel® S9 consists of highly purified sepiolite with no intentionally added substances. As a natural mineral, it may contain low-level impurities detectable semi-quantitatively via X-ray diffraction (XRD).
